					<head>Karaite commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>A Judeo-Arabic commentary on the book of Proverbs. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he">Judeo-Arabic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="80v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Commentary on Proverbs </title>
							<note>Contains Exodus 13:17-15:1, 15:22-17:7, 18:1-21:36, 22:4-30:21, 30:33-32:29, 33:12-34:26. Pointed and accentuated Hebrew text, with a translation and short commentary in (Judeo-)Arabic.<p>An anonymous Arabic commentary on Proverbs, chapters 7:20-21:6. </p>
								<p>Of the Hebrew text only the opening words are given. </p>
								<p>The Hebrew text is arranged as follows: Prov. 8:1-21; 22-36; 9:1-12; 13:18; 10:1-25; 10:26-11:18; 11:19-12:12; 12:13-13:9; 13:10-14:9; 14:10-34; 14:35-15:24, 15:25-16:17; 16:18-17:9; 17:10-18:9; 18:10-19:11; 19:12-20:7; 20:8-21:3; 21:4-30. </p>
								<p>An Arabic translation is added to each verse. </p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Partially agrees with Or 2567, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">337</ref>. </filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
